                <br>
                <div>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;From the autumn of 2019, the students from poor families with archived cards in high schools and secondary vocational schools in Yulin City can directly reduce and exempt tuition fees, and quickly go through the admission procedures and related subsidies. On July 15, the reporter learned from the Yulin City Student Aid Management Office that in order to comprehensively promote the work of eliminating poverty and tackling the key problems in education in our city, realize the precise education assistance, and effectively guarantee that the students from poor households (hereinafter referred to as "students from poor households") who set up archives to support "one without missing", the city has established "city-county-township (town) -school". ‚Äù Four-tier dynamic big data comparison mechanism, for poor students to build a "green channel" to go to school, this practice is still the first in Guangxi.<br><br>
                    <span style="font-size: 2.5vh; font-weight: 550;">More Measures to Build Green Channel and Precise Subsidy</span><br>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"Accurate subsidies to build a"green channel"for students from poor families to go to school. The head of Yulin City Student Aid Management Office introduced that, under the leadership of the subsidizing department, large data comparison work was carried out in conjunction with relevant departments, and a four-tier motivation mechanism of "city-county-township-school" was established. Before the beginning of the autumn semester each year, the bottom number of students from poor households registered in schools (gardens) in Yulin City was comprehensively ascertained and verified. After that, a "green passage" will be established for poor students to go to school in an all-round way, and the admission formalities will be handled quickly. After enrollment, the highest level of grants and other related subsidies will be handled for poor students. The reporter learned from the Yulin City Student Aid Management Office that in order to standardize the work of student aid and ensure that students from poor families should do their best to help, our city has taken a variety of measures to carry out precise aid work.<br>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In order to further standardize the work of student aid, our city has also established a unified criterion for identifying students with financial difficulties from families throughout the city. The Municipal Bureau of Education actively joins the departments of civil affairs, people's associations, poverty alleviation, trade unions, disability and veteran affairs to carry out the work of identifying students'identities, and carries out quantitative evaluation of the economic situation of students' families. At the same time, we should further reduce certificates for the convenience of the people, cancel most of the student certificate materials, and reduce the phenomenon of mistake and omission of subsidies through large data comparison.<br><br>
                    <span style="font-size: 2.5vh; font-weight: 550;">At present, 240,130,000 students are subsidized.</span><br>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As of June 30, 2008, the city has raised 282 million yuan in financial aid, supported 241.3 million students, and distributed 178 million yuan in financial aid. Among them, 769,900 students have been subsidized and 67,211.11 million students have been granted.<br>
